Catch gear of mine-cage type.-A pair of spring- actuated bolts a<2> are mounted in cylinders a on the cage roof and are connected by guided chains b to the hoisting- cable. In the event of the hoisting - cable breaking, the bolts are forced into engagement with iron ladders D or with notched bars fitted in the sides of the shaft. The cage may be strengthened by a U-shaped strap A<1> through which the bolts pass. Reference has been directed by the Comptroller to Specifications 2157/87, 2061/97, 9108/07, and 14,820/07.

column12: SINTERING AIDS FOR DIELECTRIC MATERIALS CONFIGURED FOR CO-FIRING WITH NICKEL ZINC FERRITES
column13: Disclosed are embodiments of materials for microstrip and substrate integrated waveguide circulators/isolators which can be integrated with a substrate. This composite structure can serve as a platform for other components, allowing for improved miniaturization of components. In particular, a sintering aid can be used to improve the fit between a ferrite material and a dielectric material, improving performance.
